<br>
Someone had to do it sometime.  They had the forces and the skill.  Their intention was not to &quot;ruin&quot; anything for anyone else.  Think of it like this...<br>
<br>
Did ya ever play Pac Man?  Did ya ever get frustrated because there was no...&quot;end&quot; per say?  However, if you turned around and played something like Super Mario Bros, you eventually beat the boss.  It was a sense of acheivement.  <br>
<br>
In EQ we spend a lot of time killing the little mobs on the lower levels.  Some even spend a lot of time killing big mobs over and over and over again.  For someone to finally get to the &quot;end game&quot; was both a relief for them, I'm sure...as well as a sense of accomplishment.  <br>
<br>
